# Implementation Plan - Integrate Resend Email API

This plan outlines the changes needed to integrate the Resend HTTP API for sending verification and notification emails, bypassing the port 587 SMTP block on Render's Free tier.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Service

#### [MODIFY] [EmailService.java](file:///c:/Users/veere/Videos/FinBridge_Final20/backend-springboot/src/main/java/com/finbridge/service/EmailService.java)
- Add `@Value("${RESEND_API_KEY:}")` to read the Resend API key from the environment.
- Modify `sendHtml` to conditionally route emails:
  - If `RESEND_API_KEY` is provided, send via Resend REST API (using HTTP port 443, which is not blocked by Render).
  - If `RESEND_API_KEY` is empty, fall back to standard SMTP (`JavaMailSender`).
- Add a private helper method `sendViaResend` to format the request and call `https://api.resend.com/emails` using `RestTemplate`.

